'''Terrarium City''' was an [[Architect/Legends|architectural]] marvel located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]].

==History==
It was located in a natural depression on a plain, which was widened, sealed and filled with a liquid polymer. Modified [[Battleship/Legends|battleships]] above the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] would then carve sections of the now hardened polymer into living space, and this process was then repeated until 18 levels were created to form the [[City/Legends|city's]] structure.

The polymer used could later on be reshaped by the city's inhabitants, if they wanted to. This meant that most of the walls in each flat could be turned into artworks by manipulating them. Finally, the city was capped by a transparent sheet, where thin spires were used as [[Turbolift/Legends|turbolift]] shafts and waste elimination systems.

Like all of [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]] it was destroyed in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] by the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star's]] [[Superlaser/Legends|superlaser]]. During the time of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the [[Solo apartment]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] had a [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]] of Terrarium City in it.

